data.description:
BASEMENT
Home is under original warranty!
CALL NOW! 317-501-2449 or 317-774-1620

ABOUT THE HOUSE:
2880 Square Feet, 
Huge Master bedroom (19 X 17) 
Bonus room (16 X 15) has cable outlet.
Formal living room with cable hook-up and a formal dining room.
Family Room (21 X 16).  Corner vent free fireplace room is wired for surround sound and cable.  The family room flooring is bamboo.
Kitchen and the downstairs’ bathroom all have Wilsonart® laminate wood plank flooring.

Kitchen has a large 5’X5’ custom counter height island/table with lots of cabinets and drawers for additional storage while also adding seating for 6 – 8.  This eat in Kitchen (12 X 21). 
Basement is very large and open with rough ins for an additional bathroom and water softener.  Whole house humidifier attached to the furnace.  

Garage walls and ceiling are insulated and painted.  There is a lot of shelving and storage.

The Outside: This wonderful 4 bedroom comes on approximately 1/3 acre lovingly landscaped lot.  13 Tons of newly installed pea gravel means that you never have to add mulch – ever.  The patio out back is a fabulous 20 X 32 feet with wonderfully rounded steps.  It has been wired for outside speakers on either side of the patio doors.  The fenced backyard gets its shade from the large trees on the other side of the fence.  Use the 8X10 shed to store your garden equipment and lawn mower.          

20’ X 32’ Patio, grill pad - large fenced in back yard.  You have to see this in person!

Motivated seller, we can’t wait to show you this great “For Sale by Owner” home.  
Call now.  317-774-1620 or 317-501-2449.


Neighborhood Description

The Neighborhood: Welcome to Roudebush Woods, located just 5 minutes from “Our Lady of Grace” Catholic church and school, White River Elementary, Noblesville High School and Noblesville Christian School, add a minute or two and get to the library or Forest Park.  Lots of neighborhood activities to choose from.  You can see the playground and basketball court from the house.  A short walk gets you to the neighborhood pool, nice, large and heated for those early morning or late evening swims.
data.whatILove:
The upstairs bonus room is great for playing games, doing homework, an office or extra quest room.  Great for sleepovers.  I love the real bamboo flooring in the family room and the built 
in box seating that gives us more room for people to sit and keeps those backpacks and extra blankets somewhere neat to go.  The master bedroom has a great plant shelf with an outlet and a switch that allows you to put some soft lighting up there for just the right touch.  The large walk in closets are amazing.
